for behaviour: 
Participants' predictions are partly based on their 'memory span' - the sample of previous several sound sequences. This will be verified with model fitting; 
There are individual differences in their memory span; 
for explicit expectation (blocks 5-8): 
If the sample size is big enough, we will investigate whether false positives (when a global deviant is expected but none occurs in the trial) trigger P3b in individuals; if not, in group analysis. 
In there are individual differences in whether participants explicitly predict in blocks 10-13, we will explore the changes in ERP between those who do and those who do not predict.

